(6, 'Scorpius', 'Scorpius is one of the constellations of the zodiac. Its name is Latin for scorpion, and its symbol is Scorpio.svg (Unicode ♏). It lies between Libra to the west and Sagittarius to the east. It is a large constellation located in the southern hemisphere near the center of the Milky Way.\r\n<p>Scorpius contains many bright stars, including Antares (α Sco), "rival of Mars," so named because of its distinct reddish hue; β<sup>1</sup> Sco (Graffias or Acrab), a triple star; δ Sco (Dschubba, "the forehead"); θ Sco (Sargas, of unknown origin); ν Sco (Jabbah); ξ Sco (Girtab, "the scorpion"); π Sco (Iclil); σ Sco (Alniyat); and τ Sco (also known as Alniyat, "the arteries").</p>\r\n<p>Marking the tip of the scorpion''s curved tail are λ Sco (Shaula) and υ Sco (Lesath), whose names both mean "sting." Given their proximity to one another, λ Sco and υ Sco are sometimes referred to as the Cat''s Eyes.</p>\r\n<p>The constellation''s bright stars form a pattern like a longshoreman''s hook. Most of them are massive members of the nearest OB association: Scorpius-Centaurus.</p>\r\n<p>The star δ Sco, after having been a stable 2.3 magnitude star, flared in July 2000 to 1.9 in a matter of weeks. It has since become a variable star fluctuating between 2.0 and 1.6. This means that at its brightest it is the second brightest star in Scorpius.</p>\r\n<p>U Scorpii is the fastest known nova with a period of about 10 years.\r\nω¹ Scorpii and ω² Scorpii are an optical double, which can be resolved by the unaided eye. They have contrasting blue and yellow colours.</p>\r\n<p>The star once designated γ Sco (despite being well within the boundaries of Libra) is today known as σ Lib. Moreover, the entire constellation of Libra was considered to be claws of Scorpius (Chelae Scorpionis) in Ancient Greek times, with a set of scales held aloft by Astraea (represented by adjacent Virgo) being formed from these western-most stars during later Greek times. The division into Libra was formalised during Roman times.</p>', '497 sq. deg. (33rd)', 'Antares', 'Gliese 682', '18', 'SQ3', 'Zodiac', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/yXAjTeo4EyG1dn9s2MMhVInOtTQThWi9QrVTTetiksY-AO7UKjW58PqSfKGBmRxwpMpZi4vu_BUtgiLq5CnrHl7Smm52ofRrQhcB-I7RGxjCs-DlewxUsCi6AdL8F7Do5Cg1lmsbD6Rfk8NT9CKopqXgj97fAcMz1Bzp2A2FUmI6QuZpSCA8Y7P3sM1MizAOjLbqfZQB71flkkfRVUdp-MOHtKbdS4E4gOC2x2zV6vPT2o7gTfnGqGm0dNlABsjrm1RrPT8aXZ7jQQuCeg43AuaDLbjh0J5uTtlJQDQGcQShnouG-tC7JXoOaaRlXuoTgeKT0cOpamIREeFjWvwSNvUAeFTkzQnpvT06Vl2TbxHY2pKqsqRO2aFvmozXIGoXPseqt53IF9c_dlmNNnwhA5UjZRrvt62wFp1oAT_qc6jYXpWR88vnQKLRtKdIHbcNHKOqg9aN6Mn_pZpHV7xymj70cd1fb1-xeu49QqiGPPWMUfYxXa1toRmKxG_tqfmdPD3LyGmu0ePvijWaaYyv1BqTKHLD3Orip32mZloDylY=w200-h270-no', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/GY6E0cS_wZ3yA2YzrgRm9quu0K5BrfBiZ6Lyhecr5RXi0gTiy8zvTtd4LUxhgApouWgTV9ZjIO4Ixmmul9rqTHLdIROlFRM6pHDCIeWHWtfP7CmOglemp-7vl8Ixjomf1mCYxm5PdGvAywaqkJAYz0fADqYLaUM2mfRjnJwPkaUJ3bUBQjZFVL_7MgA7Rh57kvWuP_UPDt1ZfR7swM5r2vVelc7mE7lTzaZlh4nwxWKqy-kpzX_oHbD8bAFw0YkdQYz88fJkca2d4YHyxPDMxNMnYb1sxgTuI29wbJ-DCDI0M3Iodty6ikIch7EOocoNWzyQpxjI7wxinIA_sQo29uOHJW9FJMS9WtEfQ3TRh99CEaPBRtTvyTFkv9zZjL4CMLccQXa6g5fNZl6AW-drwXUFHorzY3fAKsV2Dcb6u_KgOEJOW_bk2nTo_mFRLtg-XqxRWQjwbiZIJPtmEHxcoh9N_lZumhOuAuwx5X0xrGxVQ514sBJ_JcBaDs9u9Y0Pvm7VEHXUdZx1QooDcx6N_JgIDkpElS7XFm_xzAyMCHc=w558-h799-no,https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Q02WGgXIm185-nBUt-3XYgALQHD4dEn7RApUwI101BtP73AKAroT07eiWZNVzxuFSp9aLKF63pSf-26FEB1mPVGakOAbARSa6wmFnxvstKa5YfoNDeL2Lo0aKhxmksxI0I8CR7OgTVcc8ywdElPbofOCqaVU-4-C6E4FrtNCEwJ9y9ZI70reG91-06ol8urMcLBrJapllwvqyJpTugC_QMOlvuJYkoaWPqSmCvVvEeZRh4UPyNklnq57SDvjndXFEovPL82s4yYQeji0gfKQfgrdsU4BieZSA6d4_oFI70M-dpZXyztuNRcJ4dptE6ml4XocCbKIRcydZeku68EdgWTxA7fnlVQkA2bWf2QCxQQoX68-TfR-eF7-CBUQuWY0Kaf_MIRgRC0sC7bhBwzud9fh4SqLvbvLYIHTBzX-v4R5Kd1EwCEGhELtx0K4dTiP_DlQC9PYf0fhES2quZnBAlwMCkp30AboybnJcn9Du5-dX4OKaAkPu2vUZT1c5jB67gBiMOvmxLrOITNLIGWYuLaiPMkdo3KxOvGCtkSSuyc=s799-no,https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Bw7bIS2fb41NWcmNr8yOwap_O3V5WbLjlEPZBuzedFuNCV3PehL3G